cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep learning workflow for automated segmentation of the left ventricle from CINE MRI images. The workflow involves using a Temporal Fully Convolutional Neural Network (T-FCNN) to identify LV contours across consecutive frames, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of fully-connected Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) and Semantic Flow to further refine the LV boundaries suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
